<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880202-0025 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: McDonnell Douglas Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GOVMT MD </CO><TEXT>   The National Aeronautics and Space Administration said it awarded a McDonnell Douglas Corp. unit a three-year, $54.8 million engineering-support contract.    NASA said that if it exercises additional options, the value of the contract could reach $165.2 million. The agency said St. Louis-based McDonnell Douglas, an aerospace concern, will provide engineering services for the Goddard Space Flight Center in Greenbelt, Md. </TEXT></DOC>